---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const title = "Terms of Service | Des Moines Septic";
const description = "Terms of service for desmoinesseptic.com.";
---
<Layout {title} {description}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: May 2026</em></p>
      <p>By using desmoinesseptic.com or submitting a service request through this website, you agree to the following terms.</p>
      <h2>Service Scheduling</h2>
      <p>Submitting a request through this site does not constitute a binding service agreement. We will contact you by phone to confirm details, schedule the work, and provide a final quote before any service is dispatched.</p>
      <h2>Pricing Information</h2>
      <p>Price ranges shown on this site reflect typical residential pricing in the Des Moines metro. Final pricing is confirmed by phone before service is performed. Unusual conditions, access issues, or additional services may result in different pricing than the ranges shown.</p>
      <h2>No Warranty on Informational Content</h2>
      <p>Educational content on this website is provided for general informational purposes. We make no warranty about the accuracy, completeness, or current applicability of any specific piece of advice to your individual system. For binding professional advice about your specific septic system, rely on the on-site inspection and recommendations we provide.</p>
      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, Des Moines Septic and its operators are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of this website. Liability for service work performed is governed by the terms of the service agreement signed at time of work.</p>
